HEADWORD: Dogger
<hw>Dog"ger</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[D., fr.
<ets>dogger</ets> codfish, orig. used in the catching of codfish.]</ety>
<fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A two-masted fishing vessel, used by the
Dutch.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dogger</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Dogger
<hw>Dog"ger</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A sort of stone, found in the mines
with the true alum rock, chiefly of silica and iron.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Doggerel</ent>⟦br⟧
